Sampson Itode, Port Harcourt The Ignatius Ajuru University of Education in Rivers State on Tuesday suspended a final-year student of the Department of Computer Science, Nwiroegbu Onyebuchi, for alleged rape of a female colleague. The university suspended Onyebuchi after the victim, whose name was withheld, reported the matter to the management. “The management of IAUE has suspended a male student from studies on an allegation of brutal rape of his female colleague. “His name is Nwiroegbu Onyebuchi – UE/2016/COMP/BED4/0052 – Year 4 Computer Science. “Meanwhile, the matter has been referred to the students’ disciplinary committee for further investigation,” a statement by the school’s Public Relations Officer, Ngozi Okiridu, said. Also, two other students were suspended over their alleged involvement in cultism. Okiridu identified the students as Julius Isirimah of the Chemistry Department, and Dukobo Sowanate, of the Department of Geography and Environmental Studies. She noted that Isirimah, who was rusticated for cult activities in his former school, was attacked by Sowanate and his gang members for allegedly belonging to a rival cult. “Julius Isirimah was brought to the university’s health centre almost lifeless following an attack on him by a rival cult, led by Dukobo Sowanate. “What is particularly worrisome about this matter is that Julius Isirimah was rusticated by UNIPORT because he was a member of a notorious cult. “The matter has been referred to the students’ disciplinary committee for further investigation. There is no rest for the wicked,” the statement added. Copyright PUNCH.
